hopobject.body: Remove card can a pharmacy refuse to transfer a prescription According to information received and published by The Guardian, Russia's Federal Security Service — a successor agency of the Soviet-era KGB — plans "to ensure that no communication by competitors or spectators goes unmonitored during the event." The newly amended Sorm system, which is Russia's telephone and internet spying system, has been described by experts as the NSA's "Prism on steroids."
